Defendant Tapana A Phalphouvong in court with attorney Ann Jaspers for Torrie R. Williams. Morgan Wilz, appears as intern for the state under the student practice rule under the supervision of  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Court sentences defendant to serve 1 day  in the House of Correction with credit for 1 days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.
Defendant to pay all costs, fees and surcharges by 9-11-2015 or civil judgment. 

Court will consider expungement after 6 months if defendant successfully pays all court costs.
